sub_title:
Physiotherapist at Vegter Voetfysiotherapie / 
Co-founder of Sport For Empowerment Foundation Sierra Leone
summary:
As a physiotherapist, I know how important exercising is for everybody, including children. Through my foundation, deprived children in Sierra Leone are encouraged to exercise. Our projects leverage the power of sport and education to enable young people to empower themselves to improve their own lives and those of their peers.

We believe that real development can only be realised when local communities are genuinely empowered with the tool set to drive their own development.

We are always looking for people who can support us in any way; financially, but also through the donation of materials and by sharing their skills and know-how.
